t and only character, and I chose the server pretty much at random. I understand that it is a fairly new server and currently one of the weaker ones out there. IMO, that is perfect for me. Even though I am level 58, I am still a noob in many ways. I have a lot to learn about playing my class, and a lot to learn about other classes as well.<br>
<br>
Anyway, as I have advanced up in level, I have been recruited by many guilds that are much stronger than my own, which is still growing. I have considered each offer seriously, as I don't want to limit myself blindly, but I also don't want to leave what could potentially be a very good thing either.<br>
<br>
Not long ago, morale was pretty low for us. We didn't seem to be going anywhere. Me, along with some of the other higher level folks in the guild decided to do something about it. We started placing a heavy emphasis on leveling, riding our guildies constantly about it, and now, all of a sudden, the &quot;youngsters&quot; are starting to break through to their 50's. <br>
<br>
The best thing? Everyone is very excited about where we are going. We have great chemistry as a group as well. Unfortunately, this may have cost us some members as well. The way we proposed this &quot;leveling&quot; thing to our guildies was kind of firm. In the long run, I feel like anyone who is going to be unhappy with us for any reason would be better off elsewhere. Right now, our chemistry is fantastic, and the leveling is going absolutely GREAT.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I am so glad right now that I have not gone to a higher level guild. The way mine is going, we will be there very soon ourselves. We look like a noob guild now, and we are in many respects, but we are growing fast. <br>
<br>
I think that when I got my epic, it was kind of a wake up call for everyone else. I am the first one ever to be in my guild who has an epic, and the other members are starting to think &quot;Hey! If Selane can do it, so can I. I just need to put in the hours!&quot;<br>
<br>
Anyway, I could probably be pharming primal with another higher level guild right now (or close to it), but I would not be at home.<br>
<br>
Now this isn't to say that I will be in this guild forever. You never know what is going to happen. However, at this point, there is not a guild on my server who could get me away from what we are building at our noob guild.<br>
<br>
I reccommend to everyone who is struggling with this same question that they stay where they are and give your guildies a chance. It will make the game much more fun.<br>
